---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Tailscale Guide" description="Connect the BridgeAIChat control host and agents over Tailscale.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Networking</div>
    <h1>Use Tailscale as the private fabric between the gateway and every agent.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The first public beta assumes a trusted Tailscale network. That keeps the setup private, cuts out public ingress,
      and makes it easier to point every remote device at the gateway over a stable internal address.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Gateway URL</div>
      <h2>Agent configuration</h2>
      <pre>gateway:
  url: ws://100.x.x.x:8080/agent</pre>
      <p>You can also use a MagicDNS hostname if that is enabled for your tailnet.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Checklist</div>
      <h2>Before blaming the app</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li>Confirm the gateway host and the agent device are both connected to the same tailnet</li>
        <li>Confirm the gateway process is actually running on port <code>8080</code></li>
        <li>Confirm the agent can reach the Tailscale address from the terminal</li>
        <li>Prefer private Tailscale routing over exposing the beta gateway to the public internet</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
